Since 2005, Uganda’s Constitution has been controversially amended a few times to benefit the head of State, Yoweri Museveni.
I’m sure another amendment can be made, this time to include the runner-up in the presidential election in the national political debate in Parliament and, by that, improve the quality of debate in Parliament. He says that four days since the military surrounded his home amid a tense general election in the country, his family has run out of food supplies. Museveni claims the election was the “most cheating-free” poll in Uganda’s history. This comes after the President admitted that he instigated Sonko’s removal from office over his confrontational leadership style Some tech observers, however, noted that the restoration was only partial with full access yet to be achieved. American Department of State cites reports of pre-election violence and election irregularities.